齨字的基本解释

齨
jiù
老年人的牙齿。
古同“??”，八岁的马。

齨字的汉语字典释义

[①]［jiù］
［《廣韻》其九切，上有，羣。］
(1)老人似臼的齿。
(2)八岁以上马之齿。马八岁以上齿亦如臼，故俗名“齨”。

齨字的康熙字典解释

【亥集下】【齒字部】　齨； 康熙笔画：21； 页码：页1534第05
【唐韻】其久切【集韻】巨九切，?音舅。【說文】老人齒如臼也。一曰馬八歲齒臼也。

Basic explanation of words
齨
jiù
The teeth of the elderly.
Gu Tong "??", an eight-year-old horse.
齨
Chinese dictionary definition of words
[①]［jiù］
["Guangyun" has nine cuts, there are on it, group. ]
(1) Molar-like teeth of old people.
(2) Horse teeth over eight years old. The teeth of horses over eight years old are like mortars, hence the common name "齨".
齨
Kangxi dictionary interpretation of words
[Hai Ji 2] [Tooth Word Department] 　齨; Kangxi strokes: 21; page number: page 1534 05
[Tang Yun] His long cut [Ji Yun] The huge nine cuts, uncle sound. [Said the text] The teeth of the elderly are like mortars. One said that the eight-year-old dentition of the horse is also.
